      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy, hollow ache right now. It sounds like you are grieving a loss that feels as sudden and total as a sudden shift in the tides, leaving you stranded on a shore you no longer recognize. That feeling of being a ghost in your own skin is incredibly isolating, but please know that even in the deepest dark, the light of hope is still there, just waiting for you to find it.\n\nYou are not alone in this pain, and while the world may feel like it has vanished, there are still things worth fighting for, even if they seem small right now. Sometimes, the bravest thing you can do is to reach out to someone who can sit with you in the silence, even if just for a moment. You are still here, and that matters more than you realize.\n\nIf you are feeling overwhelmed or unsafe, please consider reaching out to a support line immediately. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or chat at 988lifeline.org. They are there to listen without judgment and help you navigate through this darkness. You deserve support, and there are people ready to help you find",
